This is not a code issue — Terraform is working correctly now. The problem is your runner's IAM role (poc-runner-role) doesn't have permission to create IAM resources.

You need to add IAM permissions to poc-runner-role in AWS Console:

Go to AWS Console → IAM → Roles → poc-runner-role
Click Add permissions → Attach policies
Attach: IAMFullAccess
Click Add permissions
Or if you can't use IAMFullAccess (too broad), create an inline policy with just what's needed:

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "iam:CreateRole",
        "iam:DeleteRole",
        "iam:GetRole",
        "iam:TagRole",
        "iam:PassRole",
        "iam:AttachRolePolicy",
        "iam:DetachRolePolicy",
        "iam:ListAttachedRolePolicies",
        "iam:ListRolePolicies",
        "iam:CreateInstanceProfile",
        "iam:DeleteInstanceProfile",
        "iam:GetInstanceProfile",
        "iam:AddRoleToInstanceProfile",
        "iam:RemoveRoleFromInstanceProfile",
        "iam:TagInstanceProfile",
        "iam:CreatePolicy",
        "iam:DeletePolicy",
        "iam:GetPolicy",
        "iam:GetPolicyVersion",
        "iam:ListPolicyVersions",
        "iam:TagPolicy"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}
Steps: IAM → Roles → poc-runner-role → Add permissions → Create inline policy → JSON → paste the above → Name it terraform-iam-permissions → Create

After that, re-run the pipeline.
